io.github.mywarp.mywarp.warp

Interface Warp

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Warp>

    public interface Warp
extends java.lang.Comparable<Warp>
    A named location with additional meta-data. Two Warps are equal if and only if their names are equal.

    Use a WarpBuilder to create instances.

        java.util.UUID getWorldIdentifier()
        Gets the unique identifier of the world this warp is positioned in.

        The loaded world identified by the identifier can be acquired from the Game by calling Game.getWorld(UUID). There is however no guarantee, that a warp's world is actually loaded, calling Game.getWorld(UUID with the unique identifier returned by this methid m retun an empty Optional.
